name: Classic Snake Plant (Laurentii)
description: When you think of snake plants it's likely the easily-recognizable Dracaena trifasciata 'Laurentii' that comes to mind. Sometimes called the variegated snake plant or striped mother-in-law's tongue this popular hardy species stands out for its striking foliage patternation.

name: Philo Pink Princess
description: Striking bright pink variegation contrasts against its dark green or maroon leaves.This philodendron has a climbing growth habit and its variegation requires high humidity and bright indirect light.

name: Philo White Knight
description: Its long pointed green leaves are splashed with light green and stark white variegation.

name: Philo Silver Sword
description: This climbing philodendron gets its common name from its silvery sword-shaped leaves.

name: Philo Brasil
description: It is distinguished by its lime green to yellow variegation.

name: Philo Ring of Fire
description: With long broadly toothed leaves having bright orange pink red yellow or many hues of green.

name: Philo Painted Lady
description: It shows off bold striking leaves like they are streaked with a brush. The bright large yellow foliage is speckled with green and displays pink petioles.

name: Philo Jose Bueno
description: Add a tropical feel to your plant collection with large thick variegated leathery leaves with splashes of yellow gold cream or white hues.

name: Philo Rio
description: It is a type of Philodendron Brasil; the plant displays narrow shiny green cream and gray variegation on the foliage.

name: Philo Strawberry Shake
description: It is a stunning variegated houseplant that is known for its unique pink yellow and cream coloring.

name: Philo White Stripe
description: Leggy philodendron typically with a white stripe down the middle.

name: Philo Billietiae
description: While this Philodendron plant can grow up to five feet tall its leaves are significantly impressive. They can reach three feet long and ten inches wide so plant lovers should ensure their Billietiae has plenty of space.

name: Philo Heartleaf Varigated
description: Variegated is an attractive houseplant because of its beautiful heart-shaped leaves and low-maintenance needs.

name: Philo Mamei
description: a beautiful tropical plant to own. Its heart-shaped bright green leaves show silver markings resembling smudges and giving it a cloud-like appearance

name: Philo Moonlight
description: The Moonlight Philodendron is a non-vining variety and typically grows in clumps as a dense shrub-like plant. Even so Moonlight can reach up to two feet tall and over two feet wide at maturity. New leaves come in lime green or bright yellow with the color losing intensity as it grows and eventually altering to a darker green.

name: Philo Micans Variegated
description: Growing philodendron with pink white and green variegation.

name: Monstera Deliciousa
description: The large foliage of the mature plants has striking fenestration and this exotic-looking plant is super easy to grow indoors. Individual leaves grow to be up to 3 feet long and with its upward vining growth habit and aerial roots it grows best up against a pole or trellis.

name: Monstera Thai Constellation
description: The splotchy creamy white and yellow pattern on the fenestrated foliage results in a unique form of variegation that for some enthusiasts makes it a worthwhile investment.

name: Monstera Albo
description: It looks similar to 'Thai Constellation' but the splotchy white patterns can develop to be pure white on some leaves of mature specimens.

name: Monstera Peru
description: If you're looking for a compact monstera with beautiful individual patterns on its thick foliage consider the variegated variety of the Monstera Peru. Just remember that this plant won't develop fenestrations on its foliage regardless of how mature it is.

name: Monstera Mint
description: The mint Monstera is a variegated variety of Monstera that has a unique and attractive mint coloring setting it apart from other variegated plants which often have yellow or white flecks of color.

name: Monstera Standleyana
description: This rare compact monstera species stands out for its unusual and unpredictable individual foliage color variations.

name: Monstera Half Moon
description: High Variegated White Monstera Adansonii Albo in a Nursery Pot - Half-Moon Swiss Cheese Variegated Plant

name: Monstera Aurea
description: The Aurea features the same attractive foliage as the other non-variegated Monsteras but with the addition of some fairly spectacular yellow variegations.

name: Pothos Marble Queen
description: The marble queen pothos can sometimes be mistaken for the golden pothos as the leaf detail is similar. However this variety can be distinguished by its white/cream variegation. It is a highly variegated variety that requires a bit more light than the golden pothos in order to keep its variegation bright.

name: Pothos Golden
description: Likely the most widely available pothos on the market the golden pothos is characterized by waxy heart-shaped green leaves with yellow variegation. It is considered a fast grower and does well in a variety of light conditions—from low light to bright indirect light.

name: Pothos Harlequin
description: One of the rarest pothos available the harlequin pothos displays highly variegated white and dark green foliage. It looks very similar to the manjula pothos although it does not have any cream/yellow coloring. It requires bright indirect light in order to support its bright variegation.
